JavaScript: window.frames returns a reference to the window itself! In order to fix this, also had to add:  - windows can be used as functions in IE  - frames retrieved in the window\'s fallback getter should be proxied  - XML-in-HTML processing should occur in the window\'s fallback getter  - frames can be referenced by index directly on the window Also had to introduce a small regression (see HTMLFrameElementTest.frames()): FF emulation should be able to distinguish between "window.foo" and "foo" (where "foo" is the ID of a DOM element) and return "undefined" in the first case and the DOM element in the second case. Bug 2089599: Move from using a global ContextFactory to using a per-JavaScriptEngine ContextFactory, so that we can configure each JS engine differently within a single JVM. The only user-facing change required was to make the static WebClient methods getJavaScriptTimeout() and setJavaScriptTimeout() non-static.

JavaScript: add support for document.compatMode. YUI.imageLoader.testFoldCheck() is marked as an expected failure because it depends on pixels calculations, part of a beta YUI, and it is not the time to fix now.

Make HtmlUnitContextFactory\'s getTimeout(), setTimeout(), getDebuggerEnabled(), setDebuggerEnabled() and putThreadLocal() non-static; will allow us to move to a per-WebClient or per-JavaScriptEngine ContextFactory model more easily, if we decide to do so (which in turn would make it easier to use multiple WebClient instances within a single JVM). See bug 2089599. Note: no need to deprecate anything first, because this is part of our private API.

Changed the interface for the "Dom" classes in the "html" package so they don\'t have all the non-standard Element interface.  This was done by factoring out DomNode from HtmlElement in the html package and fixing the derivation points.  (Document still derives from HtmlElement since it is overloaded for the DOM Document and root element nodes.)  A corresponding change was made in the javascript/host package by factoring out NodeImpl from HTMLElement and fixing derivation points. The DOM navigation methods in DomNode were changed to return DomNode as well.  The node creation interface was changed to create DomNodes.  The JavaScript configuration file was factored.

Fixed broken behaviour in Input.onclick.  Previously, if the onclick handler for a submit input didn\'t return true then the form would not be submitted. The html spec doesn\'t seem clear on this but Internet Explorer and Mozilla both allow the form to be submitted no matter what is returned from Input.onclick.
